Squamous metaplasia of the peritoneum.
 The capacity of the peritoneal serosa to undergo metaplasia to mullerian-type epithelium is well recognized.
 We report a case of squamous metaplasia of the peritoneum that was studied by light microscopy.
 Immunohistochemical techniques, and electron microscopy.
 The pathogenesis of peritoneal squamous metaplasia is obscure, but may be a response to chronic irritation.
